<event name="GB_STOREEVENT_SEPARATIST_NANO" unique="true">
	<beaconType id="map_icon_store_separatist" global="false">
		<color r="215" g="255" b="200" a="1"/>
	</beaconType>
	<text>To your surprise, there is indeed a Separatist ship transmitting the trade beacon. Though it doesn't appear that anything's amiss as the Separatist ship simply drifts around silently near you. You attempt to hail but you do not hear anything besides the crackle of the radio communicator and a faint buzzing sound. Preliminary scans does not answer any questions either as the ship, despite being fully functional and responsive, is devoid of any lifesigns.</text>
	<ship load="SHIP_SEPERATIST_NANOCLOUD" hostile="false" />
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Attempt to salvage the ship</text>
		<event>
			<text>The mystery of what happened to the crew of this trader doesn't matter to you. The thoughts of what may be stowed onboard in its cargo holds and the riches that may be left inside is alluring... but before you can board the ship it begins taking defensive patterns and powering up its weapons!</text>
			<ship hostile="true"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="COMBAT_CHECK" />
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Try to communicate and offer to trade.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You attempt to hail again but all you can pick up is the same buzzing sound. For no harm of trying, you ask if its willing to trade.</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event>
					<text>You hear a faint buzzing sound in reply and your terminal recieves access to the Separatists digital kiosk to trade or buy from. It seems they're open for business.</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event>
							<text>The ship opens a digital interface, and displays its wares for you to browse.</text>
							<store>STORE_BALLISTIC_STANDARD_COILGUN</store>
						</event>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true" req="LIST_CREW_SLUG">
