<textList name="GB_REQUISITION_WEAPON_TEXT">
	<text>In accordance with the Federation Requisition Act, all civilians must comply and transfer over any former Federation ship mounted weaponry during wartime. Fortunately, most civilians do not mind parting ways with these often outdated weapons.</text>
	<text>"Has the War really been that bad? We... understand. If it means we're one step closer to normalcy, then I can part ways with this." They comply and transfer over the expected weapon.</text>
	<text>"It would make better use out there on the front than back here shooting at the occasional pirate or forward scout I 'spose." A weapon is jettisoned off the ship.</text>
	<text>You are met with silence. You weren't sure if this was going to be another runner, and begin to weigh your options until suddenly the ship jetissoned a weapon. You do not attempt to hail the civilian any further.</text>
	
	<!--R4:For now will just throw these here. Taking inspiration directly from some other mods and starwars series I've seen recently -->
	<text>The civilians open their holds and release a stowed weapon, but only after scanning your ship thrice over in an attempt to verify the situation. They refuse to make any further contact.</text>
	<text>"Ahm, yes sure, we will do everything to support the war effort... all hail the Federation." You sense a bit of sarcasm, but everything else goes routinely.</text>
</textList>

<textList name="GB_REQUISITION_NONCOMPLIANCE_TEXT">
	<text>It appears they may have muted their comms as none of your hails have been responded to.</text>
	<text>"I've already lost enough to this war and I do not wish to lose anything else. Please leave us alone." The civilian ship had broke all communications with you.</text>
	<text>You transmit a copy of your documents and demand that the civilians transfer a weapon. An unhappy captain appears on screen! "What is this nonsense? We can barely defend ourselves in this ever increasingly hostile Universe and where have you or your Federation been this entire time when we needed you most? And now you expect US to help you!? No. We are not going to help you."</text>
	<text>The merchants refuses to comply. Maybe you can scare them into submission with a few well aimed shots...</text>
	<text>"We are no longer Federation citizens and do not accept this document of yours. Be warned that we will defend ourselves should you continue to advance towards us." It looks like we won't get anywhere with them.</text>
	<text>"What? But I had just given away my good cannon just a cycle ago! You can't do this!" Perhaps it might be best if we just leave these civilians alone...</text>
</textList>
<textList name="GB_REQUISITION_STATION_NONCOMPLIANCE_TEXT">
	<text>It appears they may have muted their comms as none of your hails have been responded to.</text>
	<text>You transmit a copy of your documents and demand that the civilians transfer a weapon. An unhappy captain appears on screen! "What is this nonsense? We can barely defend ourselves in this ever increasingly hostile Universe and where have you or your Federation been this entire time when we needed you most? And now you expect US to help you!? No. We are not going to help you."</text>
	<text>The merchants refuses to comply. Maybe you can scare them into submission with a few well aimed shots...</text>
	<text>"We are an independent, neutral station and do not accept this document as we are not under Federation control. We advise you cease to any attempts to commandeer any of our equipment."</text>
</textList>

<textList name="GB_REQUISITION_ATTACK_TEXT">
	<text>Looks like a display of good old Federation force is required here.</text>
	<text>Looks like a display of good old Renegade Merc persuasion is required here.</text>
	<text>You heard it all before... Maybe a few warning shots will convince them.</text>
